The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Washington, March 19: The world economy is set to contract for the first time in 60 years, the IMF warned today, as the financial crisis would lead to the global GDP shrinking by up to 1 per cent in 2009. In its latest assessment of the global economy, the International Monetary Fund said that more sustained, concerted policy actions (were) needed to revive growth in the economy across the world.                             
	 Hyderabad, March 19: Ved Jain and O.P. Vaish, the two independent directors appointed by the government on the Maytas Infra board, said they saw nothing wrong with the company that came under cloud following the Satyam scandal.                             
	 Washington, March 19: Citigroup Inc may conduct a reverse stock split as part of an exchange offer. This could give US taxpayers a 36 per cent stake in the bank. Citigroup is offering to exchange common stock for up to $27.5 billion of its preferred shares at $3.25 per share.                             
	 Mumbai, March 19: Shares of Singer India, a sick company engaged in manufacturing sewing machines, today mysteriously surged over four times on the bourses, even as brokers expressed ignorance about the rally.                            
	 Calcutta, March 19: Sony India today said its growth in 2008-09 would be lower at 20-25 per cent than the companys projections of 30 per cent for the current financial year.                                                                                                                           
